race.description: Spartan Central Coast Feb F&M Maiden Plate
race.comment: SIEBERT (9) nice filly resuming. Failed to handle the heavy track on debut and pulled up lame when seventh to Tomato Toastie over 1200m at Warwick Farm last July. Primed for this with the two sharp trials and finds a winnable contest. VILLAINESS (11) Pierro filly from the former top race mare Musidora who has been an outstanding producer including winners at black type level. Took out her most recent trial in good style over 796m at Warwick Farm. Gets map favours and shapes as the main danger. TETSU BELLE (10) Deep Field filly resuming and now in the Nathan Doyle yard. Struggled in her three runs in Victoria and has a host of gear changes for this. Impressed in both her trials and can take a hand in the finish. BRIGHT PROMISE (13) is improving with racing and should appreciate the extra trip third-up. One for the exotics.
